        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 10:09AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1009 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
southeast of Dewar, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arrowhead State Park...           Canadian...
Stidham...                        Crowder...
Raiford...                        Vivian...
Eufaula...

This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 241 and
248.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
